</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1448,2387,813,842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[1446,2658,297,1079]" box="[1448,2387,813,842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1448,2148,813,842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="46" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="3.[1446,2658,297,1079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1448,1798,848,881]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. There has never been a published field study on the Hairy Long-nosed Armadillo. Apart from records of occurrence to estimate its distribution, nothing is known aboutits natural history and conservation threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
